added.title: Grube's Fairytales
added.description: Robin tries to teach the Titans valuable life lessons by reading them fairytales, but the others co-opt his stories and spin them into their own twisted yarns.

added.title: A Farce
added.description: Brother Blood takes the Titans to trial for their recent destruction of Jump City.

added.title: Scary Figure Dance
added.description: The Titans' Halloween party is interupted by the Hive Five robbing a candy factory.

added.title: Animals, It's Just a Word!
added.description: After the other Titans are injured, Beast Boy donates his blood to save them.

added.title: BBBDay!
added.description: It's Beast Boy's birthday! But will the other Titans remember?

added.title: The Routine
added.description: Mom and the kids depart for their hard day's work, leaving a seemingly lazy Dad half-asleep on the sofa. Mom has given him one very simple job: buy mayonnaise. However, Dad manages to turn this mundane task into an epic quest, showing that his daily routine isn't as inactive as his family imagine.

added.title: The Upgrade
added.description: Gumball and Darwin see an advert for the latest, cutting-edge Bobert operating system and excitedly talk Bobert into downloading it. At first it seems like a massive improvement, but the many flaws in the new operating system become increasingly apparent.

added.title: The Comic
added.description: Gumball is the star of his own comic, but struggles to match up to his heroic alter-ego.

added.title: The Romantic
added.description: After Gumball convinces himself that Penny doesn't love him as much as she used to, he decides to put together a romantic quest to remind her of all the good times they've had together. But Gumball's romantic gesture backfires, landing Penny and maybe their relationship in serious peril.

added.title: The Uploads
added.description: Gumball and Darwin try to tear themselves away from the internet, but end up falling down the Elmore Stream-hole.

added.title: Crowbar Jones
added.description: Grizz screens an epic amateur movie he just made for a focus group. But when he notices people are leaving he must figure out ways to keep the audience engaged.

added.title: Kyle
added.description: Nom Nom is reunited with his long lost brother, Kyle.

added.title: Citizen Tabes
added.description: After accidentally wounding an animal, Ranger Tabes quits her job. The Bears do what they can to coax her out of retirement.

added.title: Dance Lessons
added.description: Panda volunteers to be Lucy's partner for a dance contest. But Panda doesn't have the heart to tell Lucy that she's a terrible dancer.

added.title: Icy Nights II
added.description: Ice Bear goes on a late-night adventure to rescue his friend, Yana, from some familiar foes.

added.title: Checkin' Out!
added.description: A trip to the supermarket has bizarre consequences.

added.title: Drama Bomb
added.description: The school play goes off the rails when the drama teacher interferes.

added.title: Watch It!
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls are tasked with keeping a priceless gem safe from thieves.

added.title: Man Up 4: The Donnyest Game
added.description: With Man-Boy on the loose, Donny must be prepared for anything.

added.title: The Oct-Father
added.description: When Princess Morbucks steals Octi, Bubbles' reaction surprises everyone, even her sisters.

added.title: Catch and Release
added.description: We finally see inside Steven's bathroom.

added.title: When It Rains
added.description: Steven helps a friend who's afraid of thunderstorms.

added.title: Back to the Barn
added.description: Steven and the Gems head back to the family barn to build some robots.

added.title: Too Far
added.description: Amethyst and Steven get in on some Gem gossip.

added.title: The Answer
added.description: Garnet finally tells Steven the story of how she came to be a Crystal Gem.

added.title: Beyond This Earthly Realm
added.description: When Finn finds a porcelain lamb, it transports him into the spirit world and only the Ice King can help get him out!

added.title: Daddy's Little Monster
added.description: Finn and Jake return to the Nightosphere to rescue Marceline and get to the bottom of what's making her act so crazy.

added.title: Gotcha
added.description: In order to do research for her tell-all memoir about men, Lumpy Space Princess goes undercover working for Finn and Jake.

added.title: Card Wars
added.description: Finn and Jake embark on an epic game of Card Quest.

added.title: Princess Cookie
added.description: Finn and Jake are called on to solve a Candy Kingdom hostage crisis when a rogue cookie takes over.

added.title: Bank Shot
added.description: Rigby has to win a bet by beating a guy at basketball bank shots.

added.title: Power Tower
added.description: Muscle Man wants to win the bodybuilding competition at his gym.

added.title: The Heart of a Stuntman
added.description: Muscle Man, Rigby, Mordecai and High Fives want to get a stuntman license for Timmy's birthday party.

added.title: New Year's Kiss
added.description: Rigby has to stop Mordecai from kissing a girl on New Year's Eve.

added.title: Portable Toilet
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get out of a portable toilet.

added.title: The Substitute
added.description: After Ms. Baker takes an unexpected personal day, she is replaced by a substitute that has a hard time handling the unruly classroom. Soon, the school day devolves into chaos and it is up to Clarence to get Mrs. Baker back to where she belongs, the classroom.

added.title: Classroom
added.description: Over the course of a single day in Ms. Baker's class, we see how Clarence and his classmates deal with their individual trials during the school day.

added.title: Dullance
added.description: Burned out from having so many adventures, Clarence struggles to sit around and do nothing.

added.title: Jeff's Secret
added.description: When Clarence discovers a new quirk about his friend, Jeff begs Clarence not to tell. Can Clarence resist the urge to expose Jeff's secret to the whole school?

added.title: Space Race
added.description: With Clarence distracted by the mysterious power of the moon, his class competes to build the highest-flying rocket. Will Sumo's homemade bucket of bolts beat Belson's store-bought rocket?

added.title: Pizza Eve
added.description: Uncle Grandpa falls for Pizza Steve's "girlfriend" and ends up in serious danger.

added.title: The Return of Aunt Grandma
added.description: Aunt Grandma is back and still bent on ruining Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: Messy Bessy
added.description: Seth must clean his room and learn to be a neater person in order to keep Messy Bessy from making his life a nightmare.

added.title: Memory Foam
added.description: When a new mattress sucks away all of Pizza Steve's memories, Uncle Grandpa and the crew must find a way to get them back.

added.title: Even More Shorts
added.description: Weird Man apprehends a dangerous foreign criminal, Belly Bag discovers a cat stuck in the RV tree, and Uncle Grandpa hosts a space exploration program on this new collection of shorts.
